-- Peter O’Brien May Join Alrosa, Aeroflot Boards, Kommersant Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-01-12T04:23:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/peter-o-brien-may-join-alrosa-aeroflot-boards-kommersant-says.html
OAO Rosneft former Vice-President
and U.S. citizen  Peter O’Brien  may become an independent
director in as many as three of  Russia ’s state-run companies,
Kommersant reported, citing people it didn’t identify.  Russia nominated O’Brien, an ex-Morgan Stanley banker who
worked on the so-called “people’s IPO” of Rosneft, as a
director on the boards of diamond miner OAO Alrosa, air carrier
OAO Aeroflot and telecommunication holding Svyazinvest, the
Moscow daily said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
